<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0236 </DOCNO><TEXT>Excerpts from a recent staff paper by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commissiontrace the growth in power generation by independent producers and examinethe regulatory policies affecting the class of producers which is independentof franchised utilities. The report recommends a relaxation of rate regulationusing cost as a basis as a way to relieve future constraints on generatingcapacity and the demonstration of new technologies. There is an overviewof current policies, the rationale for regulation, the inefficient andother problems resulting from regulation, and the advantages that a relaxationof regulation would bring to the marketing of electric power.</TEXT></DOC>